#Data Dictionary
#car: The make and model of the car. (Categorical)
#wheel-base: The distance between the centers of the front and rear wheels, in inches. (Numerical)
#length: The total length of the car, in inches. (Numerical)
#width: The width of the car, in inches. (Numerical)
#height: The height of the car, in inches. (Numerical)
#curb-weight: The weight of the car without passengers or cargo, in pounds. (Numerical)
#engine-size: The volume of the car's engine, in cubic inches. (Numerical)
#bore: The diameter of the engine cylinders, in inches. (Numerical)
#stroke: The distance the piston travels within the cylinder, in inches. (Numerical)
#compression-ratio: The ratio of the cylinder's volume at the bottom of the piston stroke to the volume at the top. (Numerical)
#horsepower: The power output of the car's engine, in horsepower. (Numerical)
#peak-rpm: The engine's maximum rotational speed, in revolutions per minute (RPM). (Numerical)
#city-mpg: The car's fuel efficiency in the city, in miles per gallon (MPG). (Numerical)
#highway-mpg: The car's fuel efficiency on the highway, in miles per gallon (MPG). (Numerical)
#price: The price of the car in US dollars. (Numerical, with some missing values)

##     precision, recall
# Prepare the data: Remove rows with missing target variable 'price'
data <- data[!is.na(data$price), ]

# Split the data into training and test sets
set.seed(123)  # For reproducibility
trainIndex <- createDataPartition(data$price, p = 0.8, list = FALSE)
trainData <- data[trainIndex, ]
testData <- data[-trainIndex, ]

# Ensure the same levels in categorical variables in training and test data
# Assuming 'car' is the only categorical variable
trainData$car <- factor(trainData$car)
testData$car <- factor(testData$car, levels = levels(trainData$car))

# Prepare the matrices for glmnet
x_train <- model.matrix(price ~ ., trainData)[, -1]
y_train <- trainData$price
x_test <- model.matrix(price ~ ., testData)[, -1]
y_test <- testData$price

# Fit Lasso regression model
lasso_model <- cv.glmnet(x_train, y_train, alpha = 1)

# Get the best lambda value
best_lambda <- lasso_model$lambda.min

# Fit the final Lasso model using the best lambda
final_model <- glmnet(x_train, y_train, alpha = 1, lambda = best_lambda)

# Get the Lasso coefficients
lasso_coefficients <- as.data.frame(as.matrix(coef(final_model)))
lasso_coefficients <- lasso_coefficients[lasso_coefficients != 0, , drop = FALSE]
print("Lasso Coefficients:")

#multiple linear regression
# Load necessary libraries
library(caret)

# Convert relevant columns to numeric if necessary (e.g., price)
data$price <- as.numeric(as.character(data$price))

# Set a seed for reproducibility
set.seed(123)

# Split the data into training and testing sets
trainIndex <- createDataPartition(data$price, p = 0.7, list = FALSE)
trainData <- data[trainIndex,]
testData <- data[-trainIndex,]

# Build the multiple linear regression model
model <- lm(price ~ ., data = trainData)

# Predict on the test set
predictions <- predict(model, testData)

# Calculate performance metrics
actuals <- testData$price
rsquare <- cor(actuals, predictions)^2
rmse <- sqrt(mean((actuals - predictions)^2))
mse <- mean((actuals - predictions)^2)
mad <- mean(abs(actuals - predictions))

# Print the performance metrics
cat("R-squared:", rsquare, "\n")
## R-squared: 0.9125956
cat("RMSE:", rmse, "\n")
## RMSE: 2625.953
cat("MSE:", mse, "\n")
## MSE: 6895630
cat("MAD:", mad, "\n")
## MAD: 1839.089
#decision tree
# Load necessary libraries
library(rpart)
library(caret)

# Define the formula for the decision tree
formula <- price ~ . - car

# Split the data into training and testing sets
set.seed(123)
trainIndex <- createDataPartition(data$price, p = .8, 
                                  list = FALSE, 
                                  times = 1)
dataTrain <- data[ trainIndex,]
dataTest  <- data[-trainIndex,]

# Train the decision tree model
treeModel <- rpart(formula, data = dataTrain)

# Make predictions on the test set
predictions <- predict(treeModel, dataTest)

# Calculate performance metrics
# R-squared
rsq <- cor(predictions, dataTest$price)^2

# RMSE
rmse <- sqrt(mean((predictions - dataTest$price)^2))

# MSE
mse <- mean((predictions - dataTest$price)^2)

# MAD
mad <- mean(abs(predictions - dataTest$price))

# Print the metrics
cat("R-squared: ", rsq, "\n")
## R-squared:  0.8692891
cat("RMSE: ", rmse, "\n")
## RMSE:  3048.634
cat("MSE: ", mse, "\n")
## MSE:  9294170
cat("MAD: ", mad, "\n")
## MAD:  2294.663
# Plot the decision tree
plot(treeModel)
text(treeModel, pretty = 0)
